news.title: Building sites faced maximum penalties for pollution: HSPCB
news.para: Till now, HSPCB has imposed nearly Rs 2 crore penalties in its anti-pollution drive focussed on ensuring a complete ban on construction, diesel generator sets, wrongly parked vehicles and vehicles running without pollution under control (PUC) certificates.

news.title: Stop construction on Khar playground: Bombay HC
news.para: “Since no construction activity can be carried out on such plot bearing survey number 1143 in terms of the said (SC) order, we restrain any further construction on such land without the leave of the court,” said the judges in their order.

news.title: Telangana collects Rs 7,000 crore from registration in last eight months
news.para: ​In the past eight months alone, the government has netted Rs 7,000 crore, which is twice the revenue earned during pre-Covid time and more than three times during the 2020-21 financial year.

news.title: Gurugram: OC applications dip by 50% in November after action against violators
news.para: Officials attribute this dip to the fear of stringent scrutiny of applications by the planning wing of DTCP apart from cancellation of sanctioned OCs by the enforcement wing over various violations.

news.title: Birla Estates to invest Rs 5,500 crore to develop project in Mumbai
news.para: Spread across 14 acres the landscape of Birla Niyaara is master planned and detailed by Sasaki and Coopers Hill respectively. The company plans to develop overall 30 acres of land parcels in phases as integrated development.

news.title: MahaRERA orders Parinee Adney's promoter to pay interest over delayed possession
news.para: The four home buyers had booked 2BHK and 3BHK flats between 2013 and 2015, and paid sums ranging from around Rs 1 crore to Rs 2 crore.

news.title: Bombay HC orders Reliance Enterprise, Builders & Developers' partners to be present in court
news.para: Yadav had booked a flat in February 2014 with M/s Reliance Enterprise, Builders and Developers for its project in Chembur (East). The Bombay high court warned it will even issue an arrest warrant to ensure their presence.

news.title: Despite complaints, defunct streetlights yet to be repaired in Dehradun
news.para: Locals say that major areas -- like Dilaram Chowk, Jakhan, several parts of the Rajpur Road, Defence Colony -- do not have proper street lighting.

news.title: Not repaired for years, roads in bad shape: Gurugram sector 38 residents
news.para: According to the residents, the roads were built in December 2016 and since then no repair work has been carried out in the area.

news.title: SC clears hurdle on custodial interrogation of ex-Unitech promoters by ED
news.para: ​The ED has sought clarification of the August 26, order of the top court by which it had transferred the Chandra brothers to two separate jails in Mumbai and said that they will participate in judicial proceedings against them through video conferencing.

news.title: Chandigarh civic body puts non-compliant board outside four societies
news.para: Earlier, Chandigarh Pollution Control Committee (CPCC) also served notices under Section 5 of the Environment (Protection) Act, 1986 for non-compliance of Solid Waste Management Rules, 2016 to these four societies.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh panel rejects Agra master plan 2031 for second time in three months
news.para: This is the second time in the past three months that the master plan draft has been rejected due to various flaws. The master plan was proposed to be implemented in March 2021.

news.title: Ludhiana: Rebate ends, few property tax defaulters come forward to pay dues
news.para: At some of the suvidha centres, one or two persons were seen making the one-time payment. Officials said 1,313 people filed their returns and Rs 44.35 lakh property tax amount was recovered on Tuesday.

news.title: Investcorp exits from INDIS Group's project in Hyderabad
news.para: Investcorp Score Fund invested Rs 135 crore in 2017 into the PBEL city project being developed by INDIS.

news.title: Pune: Gunthewari scheme relief for merged villages
news.para: The city improvement committee (CIC) of Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC) has given a nod for regularization of these properties.
